race.comment: The main race of the day, which looks a fascinating affair with a couple of runners backing up after placing in Country Cups last Friday. RICH CHAMPAGNE (5) has run a couple of third placings in BM70 grade at Sandown this time in and while this is a step up in grade, he's ready to peak third-up and has drawn beautifully. ANY LUCK (3) is the other Country Cup placegetter from last week, finishing runner-up at Coleraine, and while this looks tougher than that she was only second-up last week. GOLIOTUS (4) also rises in grade but is racing consistently and has won two of three here. KICKING KING (7) resumes. Talented typ who held his own in three-year-old listed company last campaign.
